{#
  hx-skeleton — Drupal Twig Template
  =====================================
  Renders the <hx-skeleton> web component for use in Drupal themes.

  The skeleton is purely decorative — it is always hidden from assistive
  technology via `aria-hidden="true"` on the host element. Wrap skeleton
  groups with an `aria-busy="true"` container and a `aria-live` status region
  to announce loading state changes to screen reader users.

  IMPORTANT — Boolean attributes and Lit:
    The `animated` property uses Lit's Boolean attribute type where attribute
    *presence* means true and attribute *absence* means false. The string value
    `animated="false"` is treated as true (attribute is present). To render a
    non-animated skeleton, use `data-hx-animated="false"` and attach the
    Drupal behavior below, or omit the variable entirely and keep the default.

  Variables:
    - variant    (string, optional): Shape variant. One of:
                   'text'      — Single-line text placeholder (pill shape).
                   'circle'    — Circular avatar/icon placeholder.
                   'rect'      — Rectangular content block (default).
                   'button'    — Button-shaped placeholder.
                   'paragraph' — Multi-line paragraph placeholder.
    - width      (string, optional): CSS width value. Defaults to '100%'.
                 Examples: '200px', '60%', '4rem'.
    - height     (string, optional): CSS height value. Defaults vary by variant.
                 Examples: '1rem', '48px', '3rem'.
    - animated   (boolean, optional): Whether the shimmer animation is active.
                 Defaults to true. To disable from Twig, set animated to false
                 and include the hx-skeleton Drupal behavior (see below).

  Accessibility:
    The skeleton host sets aria-hidden="true" automatically.
    Always pair skeleton placeholders with a live region:

      <div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" id="status" class="visually-hidden"></div>
      <div aria-busy="true" aria-describedby="status">
        {% for i in 1..3 %}
          {% include 'hx-skeleton.twig' with { variant: 'text', width: '80%' } %}
        {% endfor %}
      </div>

    When content loads, update the live region via JavaScript:
      document.getElementById('status').textContent = 'Patient records have loaded.';

  Usage:

    Single text line:
      {% include 'hx-skeleton.twig' with { variant: 'text', width: '60%' } %}

    Avatar placeholder:
      {% include 'hx-skeleton.twig' with { variant: 'circle', width: '3rem', height: '3rem' } %}

    Card body placeholder:
      {% include 'hx-skeleton.twig' with { variant: 'rect', width: '100%', height: '8rem' } %}

    Paragraph block (multiple lines):
      {% for i in 1..4 %}
        {% include 'hx-skeleton.twig' with {
          variant: 'text',
          width: loop.last ? '40%' : '100%',
        } %}
      {% endfor %}

    Static (no shimmer animation, requires behavior):
      {% include 'hx-skeleton.twig' with { variant: 'rect', animated: false } %}

    Loaded state (hides the skeleton and announces to screen readers):
      <div aria-live="polite" id="status" class="visually-hidden"></div>
      <hx-skeleton id="content-sk" variant="rect" height="10rem"></hx-skeleton>
      {# Set element.loaded = true from your Drupal behavior when data arrives #}

  Non-animated skeletons — Drupal behavior:
    Because Lit boolean attributes are presence-based, set animated=false via JS:

      (function (Drupal, once) {
        Drupal.behaviors.hxSkeletonStatic = {
          attach: function (context) {
            once('hx-skeleton-static', 'hx-skeleton[data-hx-animated="false"]', context)
              .forEach(function (el) { el.animated = false; });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal, once);

  Registration:
    Load the component script in your theme's .libraries.yml:
      hx-skeleton:
        js:
          path/to/@helixui/library/dist/hx-skeleton.js: { attributes: { type: module } }

    Attach the library in your template:
      {{ attach_library('mytheme/hx-skeleton') }}
#}

{% set _variant = variant|default('rect') %}
{% set _width = width|default('100%') %}

<hx-skeleton
  variant="{{ _variant }}"
  width="{{ _width }}"
  {% if height is defined and height %}height="{{ height }}"{% endif %}
  {% if animated is defined and animated == false %}data-hx-animated="false"{% endif %}
></hx-skeleton>
